'''The Great Imitator''' (also '''The Great Masquerader''') is a phrase used for [[medical condition]]s that feature [[nonspecific symptoms]] and may be confused with a number of other diseases.<ref name="Segen1992">J.C. Segen. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=FbSlyyshjOoC&pg=PA265 The Dictionary of Modern Medicine]''. CRC Press; 1992. {{ISBN|978-1-85070-321-1}}. p. 265.</ref> Most great imitators are [[systemic disease|systemic]] in nature. Diseases sometimes referred to with this name include:
* Various [[cancer]]s<ref name=Card10>{{cite book |first=Donald W. |last=Kufe |title=Holland-Frei cancer medicine |year=2009 |publisher=McGraw-Hill Medical |location=New York |isbn=978-1-60795-014-1 |pages=1–3 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=R0FbhLsWHBEC&pg=PA1 |edition=8th}}</ref> ** [[Intravascular large B-cell lymphoma]]<ref>{{cite web|first=Joseph |last=Del Paggio et al.|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/imj.13414/abstract|title=Disturbances in blood flow and 'medicine's greatest imitator'|publisher=Internal Medicine Journal|year=2017}}</ref> *Various [[Rheumatology|rheumatic conditions]], including: ** [[Fibromyalgia]]<ref>[http://www.fibromyalgia-symptoms.org/fibromyalgia_great_imitator.html Fibromyalgia as the great imitator], retrieved December 16th, 2006</ref> ** [[Psoriatic arthritis]] <ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.arthritis.org/about-arthritis/types/psoriatic-arthritis/|title=Psoriatic arthritis|date=29 Jan 2017}}</ref> ** [[Lupus erythematosus]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrongdiagnosis.com/l/lupus/intro.htm|title=Right Care|date=12 June 2014|publisher=}}</ref> ***[[Systemic lupus erythematosus]]<ref name="pmid15696465">{{cite journal |pmid=15696465 |year=2005 |last1=Bell|first1=JM |last2=Nair |first2=R |last3=Solon |first3=A |last4=Walker |first4=PD |title=SLE: The great imitator strikes again |volume=45 |issue=1 |pages=219–22 |journal=American Journal of Kidney Diseases |doi=10.1053/j.ajkd.2004.05.049}}</ref><ref name="pmid16280927">{{cite journal |pmid=16280927 |year=2005 |last1=Rooney |first1=J |title=Systemic lupus erythematosus: Unmasking a great imitator |volume=35 |issue=11 |pages=54–60; quiz 60–61 |journal=Nursing |doi=10.1097/00152193-200511000-00049}}</ref> ** [[Sarcoidosis]]<ref name="pmid17173472">{{cite journal |pmid=17173472 |year=2006 |last1=Tchernev |first1=G |title=Cutaneous sarcoidosis: The 'great imitator': Etiopathogenesis, morphology, differential diagnosis, and clinical management |volume=7 |issue=6 |pages=375–82 |journal=American journal of clinical dermatology |doi=10.2165/00128071-200607060-00006}}</ref> * [[Multiple sclerosis]]<ref>[http://www.lcmedia.com/mind366.htm Multiple Sclerosis as the great imitator] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090104140553/http://www.lcmedia.com/mind366.htm |date=2009-01-04 }}, retrieved December 16th, 2006</ref> * [[Celiac disease]]<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.mja.com.au/public/issues/181_07_041004/woo_fm.html|title=Coeliac disease: the great imitator|first=William|last=Woods|date=1 January 2004|publisher=|journal=Med. J. Aust.|volume=181|issue=7|via=eMJA}}</ref> * [[Addison's|Addison's Disease]]<ref name="pmid20609673">{{cite journal |doi=10.1016/j.amjmed.2009.12.027 |title=The Great Imitator|year=2010 |last1=Williams |first1=Penny |last2=Evans |first2=Sorcha |last3=Thachil |first3=Jecko |journal=The American Journal of Medicine |volume=123 |issue=7 |pages=e5 |pmid=20609673}}</ref> * [[Pulmonary embolism]]<ref name="pmid770102">{{cite journal |pmid=770102 |year=1976 |last1=Sharma |first1=GV |last2=Sasahara |first2=AA|last3=McIntyre |first3=KM |title=Pulmonary embolism: The great imitator |volume=22 |issue=7 |pages=4–38 |journal=Disease-a-month |doi=10.1016/s0011-5029(76)80005-3}}</ref> * Various [[Infection|infectious diseases]], including: ** [[Syphilis]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdc.gov/std/Syphilis/STDFact-Syphilis.htm|title=STD Facts - Syphilis|publisher=}}</ref> ** [[Lyme disease]]<ref>[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?sec=health&res=9F0CE3D71331F930A35753C1A965958260 NYT article on Lyme disease], retrieved December 16th, 2006</ref> ** [[Nocardiosis]]<ref name="pmid15342974">{{cite journal |doi=10.1097/01.md.0000141100.30871.39 |title=A Case Series and Focused Review of Nocardiosis |year=2004 |last1=Lederman |first1=Edith R. |last2=Crum |first2=Nancy F. |journal=Medicine |volume=83 |issue=5 |pages=300–13 |pmid=15342974}}</ref> ** [[Tuberculosis]]<ref name="http://jama.jamanetwork.com/article.aspx?articleid=331211">{{cite journal |doi=10.1001/jama.1961.63040220009017a | title=The Second "Great Imitator" - Tuberculosis | year= 1961 |last=Sivers |first=Maurice L. |journal=JAMA |volume=176 |issue=9 |pages=809–810}}</ref> ** [[Brucellosis]] ** [[Malaria]]<ref>http://www.malariasite.com/clinical-features.htm{{Dead link|date=June 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=no }}</ref> * Breathing-related sleep disorders (chiefly sleep apnea/hypopnea and upper-airway resistance syndrome). * [[Hypoglycemia]] as an imitator of a [[stroke]]. * [[Amyloidosis]].
